{
  "stem": "20581.1",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And he's the one-- this was the thank you, what he gave to the Jews.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah, well, the-- we had three synagogues.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And the rabbis, you know, to tell you who the rabbi was-- you know, that's-- we had a few of us.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But I don't remember the-- Rabbi [?",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Tauv ?] was one of them, I remember.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And the synagogues, you know, the synagogues, they were-- the-- the synagogues-- let me put it to you this way.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "The synagogues in our town was not a synagogue like in here, where it's a business, synagogue.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And the synagogue in the-- they didn't ask you if you have money or you don't have money.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Everybody who wanted to come here was more than welcome.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "We did have-- we had no professional Cantor.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "We had a rabbi which the-- the city, the town supported him.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "I mean, people who were well-to-do, we used to support the rabbi.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And we had Jewish teachers for teaching Hebrew.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "I mean, there to bar mitzvah.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And it was taken care of.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And the-- the synagogue, every Saturday it was full.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Ever holiday it was full.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "People used to come.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "Women used to come.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And children used to come.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "Everybody was OK.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And it was not like you have to belong to this center or you belong to the other center.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "It was normal thing.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "It was nothing which was out ordinary, which [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And they-- the town, the people, the Jewish people, they supported their rabbi.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And they supported this synagogue as much as they could.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And it was OK.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, Rabbi Moshe Leib, he was-- you know, he was-- he was the one-- he was very-- the way the stories go, that he was very like, a pious.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He was a very holy man.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
